'''''X-Man''''' is a [[Pornography|pornographic]] video game made for the [[Atari 2600]] by [[Universal Gamex]], designed by [[Alan Roberts (filmmaker)|Alan Roberts]] and programmed by H. K. Poon.<ref>[http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-2600-vcs-x-man_12072.html X-Man - AtariMania]</ref> It was [[1983 in video gaming|released in 1983]]. The game is unrelated to the similarly named [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] comic book series entitled [[X-Men]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mashable.com/2018/08/15/video-game-sex-scenes/#7CsKbdO4ziqR|title=The often gross and rarely steamy history of video game sex scenes|publisher=Mashable|date=August 15, 2018}}</ref>

It is the only title made by Universal Gamex.{{Citation needed|date=November 2018}} It had faced protest from women's groups when it was first released, and most retailers declined to carry the game or if they did, buyers had to be at least 18 years old to purchase the game, or it was kept [[wiktionary:under-the-counter|under-the-counter]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2018}} It could also be purchased via mail order, and an advertisement inviting such purchases appeared in at least one gaming magazine; a full-page example can be found in the July 1983 issue of ''[[Videogaming Illustrated]]''.

== Gameplay ==
In the game, the player controls a naked man in a labyrinth. The objective is to reach the door at the center of the labyrinth avoiding scissors, [[Crab louse|crabs]] or teeth. Clearing the challenge, the player enters a [[bonus stage]] simulating a sexual intercourse between the man and a woman.

